A large movement N/NE. Almost exclusively through the river valley. Movement started/was noticed when a large 'cloud' flock flew upriver, continuting to accelerate with most passing between 8 and 9 with the last decent flocks going through at c. 9:20. Three massive flocks with one extensive flock covering almost the entire length of Ribbesford Woods at one point. Very impressive! Birds counted as they passed a fixed point at the north end of the woods. The attached photo shows c935 birds (click counted via photo) which made up around c1/3rd of visible flock (which continued to the left out of frame) that I estimated at c2000 birds. Seemingly that was an underestimate!
